body: I downloaded the model, seems it's a bug in the code somewhere, still investigating

finally, found that the illegal memory access is in the Slice OP which output to id 53. Still dig more to see what happened. from now on it won't take much time since narrowed down to the right place I think.

It's CUDA Equal OP cause the issue actually.
Will have a PR today.

issue.title: CUDA Equal Greater Less can't support multi-directional broadcast

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
Fix issue https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/1591

Root Cause:
CUDA Equal Greater Less do not support multi-directional broadcast

Fix:
Add code to support the multi-directional broadcast
Also add tests to cover more cases.

body: Closing this as the fix PR is merged. Please re-open if you need further help. Thanks.

issue.title: ONNXRuntime_GPU illegal memory access error

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
Description
I encountered the illegal memory access error while using onnxruntime-gpu. But in cpu version of 
onnxruntime, the model could inference successfully.

CUDA vesrion: 10.0
CUDNN version: 7.6.5
GPU: rtx2080ti

I noticed that a similar issue occured in older version of onnxruntime, https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/1591. Actually, I was trying to convert the tacotron model (tensorflow implementation) into onnx format. I guessed that the error is caused by the broadcast mechanism, beacuse in dynamica decode step, it will send a "finished" signal in tf.contrib.seq2seq.Helper class.

Following is error message
 MemcpyFromHost node. Name:'Memcpy_8' Status Message:
terminate called after throwing an instance of 'onnxruntime::OnnxRuntimeException'
  what():  /onnxruntime_src/onnxruntime/core/providers/cuda/cuda_call.cc:97 bool onnxruntime::CudaCall(ERRTYPE, const char*, const char*, ERRTYPE, const char*) [with ERRTYPE = cudaError; bool THRW = true] /onnxruntime_src/onnxruntime/core/providers/cuda/cuda_call.cc:91 bool onnxruntime::CudaCall(ERRTYPE, const char*, const char*, ERRTYPE, const char*) [with ERRTYPE = cudaError; bool THRW = true] CUDA failure 77: an illegal memory access was encountered ; GPU=0 ; hostname=C246-WU4 ; expr=cudaEventDestroy(read_event_);
Stacktrace:

Aborted (core dumped)
